						               													<description>The third piece of the Kradia world series &amp;quot;Twilight Ravine&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Like the previous game &amp;quot;Kradia II: Wild Hunting Festival&amp;quot;, it is a stand-alone game, independent from &amp;quot;Kradia I: The Garden of Adventurers&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Kradia: Twilight Ravine (&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#169;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#169;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#180;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;) is a simple and quick party game. The game requires players to collect different cards on the field. And by hindering opponents from getting the maximum points, it will feel a bit similar to mahjong.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Compared to the gaming nature of the previous two games, the new game experience is a 180-degree shift. But similar to the game's predecessors, Twilight Ravine revolves around a group of adventurers seeking treasures. Overall, the setting is designed to complement and expand the world view of the Kradia.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
